From this last point of view, all current technologies are not good enough for us; this gives more work to algorithm designers.
That is, we have to remember not only the resolution on the X and Y axes, but also on Z.
Speed is also important, the number of frames per second.
The human movements are quite dynamic and the current 30 fps are really scarce, especially for gestures.
Steven Bathiche, from our Redmond laboratory, made a contact sensor with adjustable processing delay of 1 to 100 ms and it should be mentioned that modern serially produced sensors are closer to the second value (60-100).
