What are the main diseases of sexual transmission?
Among the ETS of bacterial origin are syphilis, chlamydia and gonorrhea.
The most common viral STDs are AIDS, human papilloma virus, genital herpes, or hepatitis.
Ladillas and sarna are among ETS transmitted by parasites.
