After tearing out large sulfur rocks, which in total weigh about 70 kilos, she carries them in two bamboo baskets that she loads on her shoulders through steep stone paths.
They are only 250 meters to the top of the volcano, which rises to 2,386 meters in altitude, but the exhausted bearers take more than 40 minutes to ascend to the turtle step, keeping the balance and slowly measuring their steps so as not to slip and fall by the precipice.
